CircuitPython external libraries (.mpy files) go here.

Install via circup (no board connection needed):

  /Users/alex/Development/PythonVEs/CircuitPython_3.13_VsCode/bin/circup \
    --path /Users/alex/Development/VsCode/CircuitPython/2026-03_Exp13_Ws2812_CPy_on_RPi-Pico-2040 \
    --board-id vcc_gnd_yd_rp2040 --cpy-version 10.1.4 \
    install <library_name>

Or use CircuitPythonSync's "Install or Update Libraries and Stubs" command.

Libraries are synced to the board via CircuitPythonSync "Copy Libs to Board".

Expected contents after install:
  neopixel.mpy           -- WS2812b driver (Milestone 2)
  adafruit_pixelbuf.mpy  -- pixel buffer base (dependency, also built-in)
